# Hemomancy spell names + descriptions (file-11 render). Auto-generated from the approved sheet.
spell-bloodlet = Bloodlet
spell-bloodlet-desc = You nick your own palm and fling the drop as a hardening needle of blood. It strikes for minor necrotic damage; the wound it opens in you is the price of every red working.
spell-clot = Clot
spell-clot-desc = You command your own blood to thicken and seal. Bleeding stops and a thin clot-scab grants brief, minor damage reduction.
spell-crimson_brand = Crimson Brand
spell-crimson_brand-desc = Your touch sears a weeping sigil into flesh. Small necrotic damage, and the brand marks the victim as bleeding — priming them for spells that feed on open wounds.
spell-hemal_spike = Hemal Spike
spell-hemal_spike-desc = Spilled blood crystallises mid-air into a long red lance and hurls itself at a target, punching through with piercing force before it bursts back to vapour.
spell-sanguine_ward = Sanguine Ward
spell-sanguine_ward-desc = A churning sheath of your own blood orbits you and drinks incoming blows, absorbing a pool of damage until it is spent.
spell-leeching_grasp = Leeching Grasp
spell-leeching_grasp-desc = You seize a foe and pull their warmth through your fingers: necrotic damage to them, a portion returned to you as healing. Pure life-theft, with no brand or wound left behind.
spell-bloodboil = Bloodboil
spell-bloodboil-desc = You set the blood of every creature in a small zone simmering. Those caught take necrotic damage in a single pulse as their own veins turn against them.
spell-scarlet_tether = Scarlet Tether
spell-scarlet_tether-desc = A thread of blood leaps to a foe and binds the two of you. While it holds, a share of the harm you suffer is paid instead from their veins.
spell-bloodbound_edge = Bloodbound Edge
spell-bloodbound_edge-desc = You sheathe your weapon in living blood. Your strikes weep extra necrotic damage for as long as you keep the rite burning.
spell-hemorrhage = Hemorrhage
spell-hemorrhage-desc = You wrench a target's circulation open and leave it gushing. Light necrotic damage on the hit, then a long, escalating bleed that drains more for every second it runs and every step they take.
spell-blood_mirror = Blood Mirror
spell-blood_mirror-desc = A film of mirror-bright blood wraps you. A portion of the damage you take is flung back along the wound that dealt it.
spell-gory_eruption = Gory Eruption
spell-gory_eruption-desc = A conditional finisher: you target a foe that is already bleeding or branded and rupture the blood within them. It bursts outward in red shrapnel that savages everything around that victim — but it does nothing to a target with no open wound to detonate.
spell-sanguine_surge = Sanguine Surge
spell-sanguine_surge-desc = You burn your own lifeblood as fuel, flooding muscle and nerve. For a time you move and strike far faster and harder — but the rite eats at your health for every second it lasts.
spell-crimson_lash = Crimson Lash
spell-crimson_lash-desc = A whip of razor blood unfurls from your hand and sweeps a wide arc, opening every throat and limb caught in the cone.
spell-exsanguinate = Exsanguinate
spell-exsanguinate-desc = A continuous arc of blood streams from a single foe to you, draining them dry. They take heavy necrotic damage over the channel; much of it heals you.
spell-vitalic_font = Vitalic Font
spell-vitalic_font-desc = You raise a fountain of shared blood at your feet. Allies who stand in its reach are knitted closed, mending wounds drawn from the pooled offering.
spell-crimson_tide = Crimson Tide
spell-crimson_tide-desc = The boil of the blood becomes a flood: a surging wave of conjured blood drowns a wide stretch of ground, battering everything within in repeated necrotic surges over several seconds.
spell-hearts_seizure = Heart's Seizure
spell-hearts_seizure-desc = You close a fist around a distant heart and crush it in one savage clench. A single burst of massive necrotic damage, and the victim is locked rigid — pulse stopped — for a heartbeat. No lingering bleed: all of it lands at once.
spell-hemoclysm = Hemoclysm
spell-hemoclysm-desc = You conjure blood from nothing and call every drop of it for a hundred paces to erupt at once — a single, unconditional cataclysm of boiling red that devastates a vast area. It needs no wounded target and no prior bleed: it makes its own.
spell-crimson_apotheosis = Crimson Apotheosis
spell-crimson_apotheosis-desc = You unmake your flesh into living blood. Wounds close as fast as they open, your blows carry a drowning red aura, and for a glorious, terrible span you are very hard to truly kill.
spell-the_last_vein = The Last Vein
spell-the_last_vein-desc = You call every enemy heart in a vast circle to empty in the same instant. Lifeblood tears free of all foes at once as catastrophic necrotic damage — and every drop pours into you, mending you in a tide of stolen vitality. Not a flood that batters and not a boil that simmers: a mass exsanguination that drains and heals.
